President Trump and President Moon of South Korea held a joint press conference in which they discussed various topics, including the upcoming U.S.-North Korea summit, trade negotiations, and the situation with China. President Trump expressed confidence in Kim Jong-un's commitment to denuclearization and stated that he would guarantee the safety of the North Korean regime. He also mentioned his disappointment with the trade talks with China and his hope for a better deal. President Moon expressed his support for the upcoming summit and his confidence in President Trump's ability to achieve a historic feat.